* predicate_memvar_parity_regression.dts
* PARITY TARGET — currently EXPECTED RED until the expression-path convergence lands.
*
* Proves $name / $a[n] resolve in the PREDICATE path (IF/WHILE/UNTIL/WHERE), not only
* in the display path (?/CALC/FORMULA). Today IF routes through the compiled WHERE
* engine (shell_eval_bool_expr -> where_boolean_eval), which does not resolve $name, so
* the PASS marker below does NOT appear yet. After the expression-path convergence
* (AIF-041: centralize predicate + expression eval on the house expr system), it does.
*
* Pass criterion:
*   BEFORE convergence: PASS markers ABSENT (known red) — the FAIL-EXPECTED marker
*                       prints, or the IF reports an evaluation error.
*   AFTER  convergence: "PARITY_predicate_memvar:PASS" and
*                       "PARITY_predicate_array_subscript:PASS" both print.
*
* This test is intentionally NOT in the default suite until the convergence lands.
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN DOTSCRIPT_PARITY
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/predicate_memvar_parity_regression.dts
*
* Self-bootstrap the environment (regression doctrine: every test sets its own
* environment; the ambient default is STOP_ON_ERROR OFF). Set it explicitly so a
* mis-resolved predicate surfaces as the FAIL-EXPECTED marker, never as an abort,
* even when run right after ERRORSTOP. ECHO OFF keeps the judged region clean.
SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

FORMULA "PREDICATE-MEMVAR-PARITY-BEGIN"

* Sanity: the SAME comparison resolves in the DISPLAY path today (must be .T.).
VAR pv = 20
? "PARITY_display_memvar_should_be_T:" + ($pv = 20)

* Target: the memvar must resolve in the PREDICATE path (IF). RED until convergence.
IF ($pv = 20)
  FORMULA "PARITY_predicate_memvar:PASS"
ELSE
  FORMULA "PARITY_predicate_memvar:FAIL-EXPECTED-UNTIL-CONVERGENCE"
ENDIF

* Target: array subscript in the predicate path. RED until convergence.
VAR pa = {10, 20, 30}
IF ($pa[2] = 20)
  FORMULA "PARITY_predicate_array_subscript:PASS"
ELSE
  FORMULA "PARITY_predicate_array_subscript:FAIL-EXPECTED-UNTIL-CONVERGENCE"
ENDIF

FORMULA "PREDICATE-MEMVAR-PARITY-END"
